message.content: cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI. The paper discusses the impact of open access on citation impact, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science such as digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybersecurity (cs.CY), cryptography (cs.CR), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the paper focuses on the impact of open access on citation impact in a specific field (condensed matter physics), it is most likely to belong to cs.DL (digital libraries) or cs.IR (information retrieval) as these sub-categories are more closely related to bibliometrics and citation analysis.
